        <div n="400-79L2" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Most of them written in 1726.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1">VIII. On seeing V<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">ERSES</hi> written upon W<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">INDOWS</hi> at I<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">NNS</hi>.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">T</hi>HE sage, who said he should be proudOf windows in his breast,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-line-2"> Because he ne'er a thought allow'dThat might not be confest;</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="3" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-line-3">His window scrawl'd by every rake,&#13;His breast again would cover;</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-400-79L2-line-4"> And fairly bid the devil takeThe diamond and the lover.400-79L2   </l></lg></div>
